This paper deals with the optimization of traffic load balancing in small cell networks, which is a subfield of computer networking (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of renewable energy sources to power base stations, which falls under the category of cyber-physical systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of cache-enabled networks, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). The optimization of network utilities involves game theory, which is a subfield of theoretical computer science (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses the energy consumption of base stations, which is a topic in computer engineering (cs.CE).
